# ===============================================================================
# Kronecker-Friendly N3 Demo (Horn/Datalog core + safe add-ons)
#
# Purpose:
#   Illustrate a “constructive / compute-by-rules” style of reasoning in N3:
#     - SECTION A is a finite, Horn-ish core (Datalog-like on finite input).
#     - SECTION B adds practical “engineering” rules, written to TERMINATE.
#
# Design notes:
#   - The core rules avoid creating new individuals.
#   - Where we *do* introduce helper nodes (reasons, auto-managers, supervisors),
#     we use log:skolem to mint DETERMINISTIC IRIs so re-firing rules does not
#     keep generating fresh blank nodes (a common cause of non-termination).
#   - No “manager-of-manager-of-...” recursive existential chains are used.
#
# Expected outcomes (high level):
#   - ex:Alice becomes an ex:Adult.
#   - Ancestor closure derives: Alice -> Bob -> Carol, so Alice ancestor Carol.
#   - Membership propagates from TeamA to OrgX, enabling canRead permissions.
#   - Proj2 gets a deterministic AutoManager and (optionally) a Supervisor.
#
# How to use:
#   Load this file into an N3 reasoner that supports:
#     - log:skolem
#     - math:greaterThan
#   Then compute the forward-chaining closure (or query for derived triples).
# ===============================================================================

@prefix ex:   <https://example.org/ns#> .
@prefix xsd:  <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix log:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#> .
@prefix math: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/math#> .

# --------------------------
# DATA (finite ground facts)
# --------------------------

ex:Alice  a ex:Person ; ex:age  "29"^^xsd:integer ; ex:memberOf ex:TeamA ; ex:parent ex:Bob .
ex:Bob    a ex:Person ; ex:age  "54"^^xsd:integer ; ex:memberOf ex:TeamA ; ex:parent ex:Carol .
ex:Carol  a ex:Person ; ex:age  "78"^^xsd:integer ; ex:memberOf ex:OrgX .

ex:TeamA  a ex:Team ; ex:partOf ex:OrgX .
ex:OrgX   a ex:Org .

ex:Proj1  a ex:Project ; ex:ownedBy ex:OrgX ; ex:hasManager ex:Bob .
ex:Proj2  a ex:Project ; ex:ownedBy ex:OrgX ; ex:needsManager true .

# -------------------------------------------
# SECTION A — "Kronecker-friendly" core rules
# -------------------------------------------

# A1) Adult classification (computable, witness-free)
{ ?p ex:age ?n .
  ?n math:greaterThan "17"^^xsd:integer
}
=>
{ ?p a ex:Adult . } .

# A2) Ancestor closure (finite on finite parent facts)
{ ?x ex:parent ?y } => { ?x ex:ancestor ?y } .

{ ?x ex:parent ?y .
  ?y ex:ancestor ?z
}
=>
{ ?x ex:ancestor ?z } .

# A3) Membership propagates up the org tree
{ ?p ex:memberOf ?team .
  ?team ex:partOf ?org
}
=>
{ ?p ex:memberOf ?org } .

# A4) Authorization: Org members can read Org-owned projects
{ ?p ex:memberOf ?org .
  ?proj a ex:Project ;
        ex:ownedBy ?org
}
=>
{ ?p ex:canRead ?proj } .

# A5) Explanation breadcrumb (NO fresh blank nodes)
#     Use log:skolem to mint a stable node for the explanation.
{ ?p ex:canRead ?proj .
  ?proj ex:ownedBy ?org .
  ?p ex:memberOf ?org .

  # Make a deterministic IRI for this (person, project) reason node:
  (?p ?proj "reason") log:skolem ?reasonNode .
}
=>
{ ?p ex:reason ?reasonNode .
  ?reasonNode a ex:Reason ;
              ex:for ?proj ;
              ex:because "memberOf(org) & ownedBy(org)" .
} .

# ----------------------------------------------------
# SECTION B — Engineering add-ons (safe / terminating)
# ----------------------------------------------------

# B1) Auto-manager creation (terminating)
#     If a project needs a manager, assign a deterministic "AutoManager" IRI.
#     Re-firing adds no new facts (same skolem IRI each run).
{ ?proj a ex:Project ;
        ex:needsManager true .

  # Deterministic manager IRI for this project:
  (?proj "AutoManager") log:skolem ?m .
}
=>
{ ?proj ex:hasManager ?m .
  ?m a ex:Person ;
     ex:role "AutoManager" .
} .

# B2) Supervisor (safe, depth-1, still terminating)
#     Create at most one supervisor per manager, and DO NOT make the supervisor
#     itself a manager (so no infinite chain).
{ ?proj ex:hasManager ?m .

  # Deterministic supervisor IRI for this manager:
  (?m "Supervisor") log:skolem ?s .
}
=>
{ ?m ex:hasSupervisor ?s .
  ?s a ex:Person ;
     ex:role "Supervisor" ;
     ex:supervises ?m .
} .
